The permittee shall furnish a final reclamation report which includes the following:
The terms of the original surface mining permit and all subsequent modifications;
A summary of the original mining and reclamation plan and all subsequent modifications;
A statement summarizing any departures from the mining and reclamation plan and the reasons for them;
A statement summarizing any problems encountered during the progress of mining work or reclamation work, and the measures taken to correct these problems;
The total acreage of land disturbed and reclaimed;
The status or condition of areas progressively reclaimed since the initiation of mining work in the area; and
A final map that is consistent with the original mining and reclamation map required by § 15-822(b) of this subtitle.
